1
00:00:01,929 --> 00:00:02,979
Previously:

2
00:00:03,729 --> 00:00:06,429
Angel's son is part of
the prophecy and sought by many.

3
00:00:06,730 --> 00:00:07,849
- Adorable.
- Sweet.

4
00:00:08,529 --> 00:00:10,779
- The baby.
- I meant the hot mama.

5
00:00:10,929 --> 00:00:13,000
She's an extraordinary young woman.

6
00:00:16,329 --> 00:00:18,960
- We got a term in Pylea: kyrumption.
- I know.

7
00:00:19,329 --> 00:00:22,170
Everyone is very anxious
for Her Majesty...

8
00:00:22,929 --> 00:00:25,530
- ...to com-shuk with the Groosalugg.
- Sounds dirty.

9
00:00:25,929 --> 00:00:27,300
It's not terrible, it's wonderful.

10
00:00:28,929 --> 00:00:31,879
- Your visions will pass to me.
- I can't give them up.

11
00:00:32,530 --> 00:00:33,579
- Cordelia.
- What about her?

12
00:00:34,329 --> 00:00:36,750
Let her know what's inside.
Don't miss that shot.

13
00:00:37,329 --> 00:00:40,000
You've become a truly
extraordinary woman.

14
00:00:41,530 --> 00:00:43,350
- I think that we--
- Groo?

15
00:00:43,929 --> 00:00:46,070
Yes, we grew closer....

16
00:00:46,929 --> 00:00:48,609
- Groo!
- Princess!

17
00:00:48,729 --> 00:00:51,399
- Oh, God!
- He just showed up.

18
00:00:52,329 --> 00:00:53,979
I thought she was meant
to be with Angel.

19
00:00:54,729 --> 00:00:55,600
I'm gonna check on Connor.

20
00:00:55,929 --> 00:00:57,539
- He's sleeping.
You can't predict those things.

21
00:01:12,730 --> 00:01:15,780
- It's strange.
- Hmm....

22
00:01:17,530 --> 00:01:19,560
I remember him being taller.

23
00:01:19,930 --> 00:01:21,189
A trick of the light.

24
00:01:21,730 --> 00:01:25,140
They don't actually get smaller
till they're very, very old.

25
00:01:26,530 --> 00:01:28,140
- I didn't mean the baby.
- I know.

26
00:01:28,329 --> 00:01:30,650
- I meant the Groosalugg.
- I know you did.

27
00:01:31,329 --> 00:01:35,469
He seem-- I don't know, short?

28
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:37,319
Oh, absolutely.

29
00:01:38,530 --> 00:01:41,269
Clearly, the guy shrank.
All over, probably.

30
00:01:41,530 --> 00:01:43,599
He's nothing but a muscly midget.

31
00:01:44,530 --> 00:01:48,640
Once Cordelia gets him home,
she'll just pop him in a small drawer.

32
00:01:49,329 --> 00:01:51,469
She took him home?

33
00:01:51,730 --> 00:01:56,650
Good. We won't have to put him up.
Place was turning into a hotel.

34
00:01:57,730 --> 00:02:01,099
- You don't have a problem with that?
- Of course not. Why?

35
00:02:03,129 --> 00:02:07,629
Because I don't remember you wearing
perfume when you left this evening.

36
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:12,259
- There may have been some magic.
- You see?

37
00:02:12,729 --> 00:02:15,639
Actual magic, Lorne.
Whatever happened was a spell.

38
00:02:16,330 --> 00:02:18,680
There's nothing between
Cordelia and me.

39
00:02:19,330 --> 00:02:23,650
Sure there is. It's got arms like
steel cables and ironic timing.

40
00:02:24,129 --> 00:02:27,009
No, it's good the Groosalugg
showed up.

41
00:02:27,729 --> 00:02:30,469
Cordelia deserves a champion.
Now she's got one.

42
00:02:31,330 --> 00:02:32,939
- What about you?
- I'm fine.

43
00:02:33,129 --> 00:02:35,159
I've been solo
most of my 240 years.

44
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:38,900
When I wasn't, it never went well.
I like being alone.

45
00:02:39,729 --> 00:02:43,379
Fine, Miss Garbo.
Have it your way. Be alone.

46
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:05,509
- So you got deposed, huh?
- Yes.

47
00:03:07,050 --> 00:03:09,650
- That sucks.
- The people turned against me.

48
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:12,610
- They'll do that.
- Endless committees formed.

49
00:03:13,650 --> 00:03:17,060
They splintered into factions.
The factions into coalitions.

50
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:19,000
Coalitions into subcommittees.

51
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:23,229
Until the radical elements,
spurred by a charismatic leader...

52
00:03:23,849 --> 00:03:26,129
...did the dance of revolution.

53
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:34,419
- And here you are.
- Yes.

54
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:39,889
So, you don't miss it?

55
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:44,930
You know. The power, castle...

56
00:03:46,050 --> 00:03:48,050
...concubines...

57
00:03:48,449 --> 00:03:50,199
...and the royal chippies.

58
00:03:53,849 --> 00:03:55,569
There was never anyone else.

59
00:03:57,449 --> 00:03:59,909
- Oh.
- I welcomed the overthrow.

60
00:04:00,449 --> 00:04:04,280
The tedium of government was hard
to bear after battlefield life.

61
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,139
But your heart wasn't in it.

62
00:04:09,449 --> 00:04:12,430
No. That left when you did.

63
00:04:40,649 --> 00:04:41,879
Princess?

64
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:44,589
Something wrong?

65
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:45,009
Hey.

66
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:49,689
- Morning.
- You the only one here?

67
00:05:50,449 --> 00:05:51,779
So far.

68
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:55,310
- How's young Connor today?
- He's good.

69
00:05:56,449 --> 00:05:58,699
Cordelia's usually in by now,
isn't she?

70
00:05:59,449 --> 00:06:02,959
I imagine she and Groosalugg
were up late catching up.

71
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:05,439
Right.

72
00:06:06,649 --> 00:06:07,810
They.

73
00:06:08,449 --> 00:06:11,779
I was hoping we could talk
before the others got here.

74
00:06:12,649 --> 00:06:14,470
Sure. What is it?

75
00:06:16,850 --> 00:06:18,110
Well...

76
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,899
...it's the fact of him.

77
00:06:24,649 --> 00:06:28,370
His sudden arrival was something
we all needed to digest.

78
00:06:28,850 --> 00:06:31,240
- There are questions.
- You're suspicious.

79
00:06:31,850 --> 00:06:34,939
- Cautious might be a better word.
- You think he's evil.

80
00:06:36,050 --> 00:06:38,509
- Evil?
- Okay, maybe not evil.

81
00:06:39,050 --> 00:06:43,860
But he's definitely hiding something.
He seem shorter to you?

82
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:50,329
We are talking about Connor,
aren't we?

83
00:06:51,050 --> 00:06:53,300
- What about Connor?
- He shouldn't exist.

84
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:56,819
His birth was foretold.
How many can say that?

85
00:06:57,649 --> 00:07:02,250
He has a role to play, that's true.
We still don't know what that role is.

86
00:07:03,050 --> 00:07:06,699
We can't be afraid to ask the
questions. His enemies won't be.

87
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:10,339
You're right. We should be prepared.

88
00:07:11,449 --> 00:07:12,959
I'm glad you agree.

89
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:17,149
Without the Nyazian prophecies,
we must look elsewhere for answers.

90
00:07:18,050 --> 00:07:21,699
We know where they went.
It's time to assault Wolfram and Hart.

91
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:25,370
That might not be necessary yet.
There are other sources.

92
00:07:25,850 --> 00:07:28,689
Ancient works accumulate
scholarship, commentary.

93
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:32,779
- You think somebody has done the work.
- That's my hope.

94
00:07:33,649 --> 00:07:37,160
I've been looking into it.
I felt you should know.

95
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:41,009
- I want to be involved. Completely.
- Involved with who?

96
00:07:41,449 --> 00:07:42,569
You're here...

97
00:07:45,649 --> 00:07:47,649
...and so is he.

98
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:52,589
Angel, your weapons
are most impressive.

99
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:56,300
Thanks. Thank you.

100
00:07:57,649 --> 00:08:00,629
Can you ask him
not to handle my weapons?

101
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:05,959
Relax. If there's one thing Groo
knows, it's how to handle a weapon.

102
00:08:06,649 --> 00:08:09,949
Poor guy. Looks like
that's about all he'll be handling.

103
00:08:10,850 --> 00:08:12,569
You mean, you two didn't...?

104
00:08:12,649 --> 00:08:17,040
I got him home last night,
and we started-- You know.

105
00:08:19,850 --> 00:08:22,759
But then, I couldn't go
through with it.

106
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:25,279
- You couldn't?
- No.

107
00:08:25,850 --> 00:08:28,480
Not after seeing
that disgusting spiny thing.

108
00:08:30,649 --> 00:08:32,470
- Spiny?
- Right up in my face.

109
00:08:33,049 --> 00:08:35,080
That's what the visions are like.

110
00:08:35,450 --> 00:08:38,750
No pain, less artsy, sometimes floaty,
and often stinky.

111
00:08:39,649 --> 00:08:42,250
- You had a vision?
- Yeah. Big as life.

112
00:08:42,649 --> 00:08:47,070
Last night, while we were getting
reacquainted. Kind of a mood killer.

113
00:08:48,049 --> 00:08:50,440
- You should have called one of us.
- Oh, please.

114
00:08:51,049 --> 00:08:54,490
Like I'd bother you because
I want sex and can't have it.

115
00:08:55,250 --> 00:08:56,830
I meant the vision.

116
00:08:57,649 --> 00:09:01,830
Oh, that. Well, it's not rising up
till sometime later today.

117
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:07,470
- Oh. Why can't you have sex?
- I could lose my vision-ity.

118
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:12,490
- If you want to play it that way.
- Vision-ity. The visions.

119
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:16,799
When that one hit me last night,
it hit me. In Pylea...

120
00:09:17,450 --> 00:09:20,960
...the visions were to pass
to Groo if we did the com-shuk.

121
00:09:21,649 --> 00:09:24,600
- How do I know that won't happen here?
- You don't.

122
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:27,950
Your transformation
could have changed that.

123
00:09:28,850 --> 00:09:31,549
Still, you know,
better safe than sorry.

124
00:09:33,649 --> 00:09:36,490
- You're doing the right thing.
- I know. I know.

125
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:42,129
I can't risk it.
It's just, I'm so....

126
00:09:45,049 --> 00:09:46,700
And he's such a....

127
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:51,110
Don't you think?

128
00:09:51,649 --> 00:09:53,190
- Yeah, sure.
- Certainly.

129
00:09:53,450 --> 00:09:55,549
There's gotta be things we can do...

130
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:58,870
- ...to relieve the tension.
- Jogging.

131
00:09:59,450 --> 00:10:02,570
- Perhaps a paranormal prophylactic.
- Because jogging--

132
00:10:03,049 --> 00:10:07,120
I guess we could probably com
without actually shuking.

133
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:13,009
That could be a slippery slope that
once you're on, that you could slide.

134
00:10:13,850 --> 00:10:16,379
At least I won't upset
the average here.

135
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:19,759
Nobody in this office
is ever gonna get any.

136
00:10:26,289 --> 00:10:27,549
It's funny.

137
00:10:29,289 --> 00:10:30,899
- The way I chew?
- No.

138
00:10:31,090 --> 00:10:34,600
Until that kiss, I thought you
and Wesley had a thing.

139
00:10:35,289 --> 00:10:36,409
- Wesley?
- Yeah.

140
00:10:37,090 --> 00:10:39,299
No, we're just good friends.

141
00:10:40,690 --> 00:10:43,529
- You want another order of those?
- Yes, please.

142
00:10:43,690 --> 00:10:47,019
Oh, no. Wait. No, I'm not hungry.

143
00:10:47,889 --> 00:10:49,990
You sure? I love watching you eat.

144
00:10:51,490 --> 00:10:52,720
Wow.

145
00:10:53,889 --> 00:10:56,909
We should probably go.
People might start to talk.

146
00:10:57,490 --> 00:11:01,529
- Why would they?
- Well, you know, us.

147
00:11:02,289 --> 00:11:05,379
"Us" has been doing breakfast for
weeks now. Everyone knows.

148
00:11:05,889 --> 00:11:10,700
But now that we've kissed, things are
different. I mean, they are, right?

149
00:11:11,889 --> 00:11:13,360
Oh, yeah.

150
00:11:19,690 --> 00:11:21,970
So you don't think they can tell?

151
00:11:22,690 --> 00:11:23,919
From here?

152
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:27,580
I'm sorry.
I'm being ridiculous, I know.

153
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:33,250
I don't have much experience with
this. I spent five years in a cave.

154
00:11:34,090 --> 00:11:36,759
- I know what that's like.
- How could you?

155
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:40,179
Because now, everything's so bright,
my eyes hurt.

156
00:11:44,289 --> 00:11:45,409
Here you go.

157
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:47,600
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

158
00:11:51,490 --> 00:11:54,539
- How will we work this?
- Like always. We'll split it.

159
00:11:55,090 --> 00:11:58,950
But you hardly ordered anything.
I'd be getting so much more value.

160
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:02,879
I think I'm making out okay.

161
00:12:09,490 --> 00:12:10,649
- Wesley.
- Wesley.

162
00:12:11,610 --> 00:12:15,230
We've identified the demon from
Cordelia's vision as a Senih'D.

163
00:12:16,409 --> 00:12:18,409
It'll rise in the mid-city area...

164
00:12:18,809 --> 00:12:20,419
...sometime before nightfall.

165
00:12:23,009 --> 00:12:26,309
The Senih'D manifests
physically for one purpose.

166
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:28,330
- Seen it.
- To feed.

167
00:12:28,409 --> 00:12:33,080
Upon rising, it'll search for a victim.
We've got to keep it from finding one.

168
00:12:33,809 --> 00:12:37,600
Angel will take the sewer.
The rest will go to Sorenson Park.

169
00:12:38,610 --> 00:12:41,000
We'll enter the underground,
double back.

170
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:44,309
- By the time we meet up--
- I know this creature.

171
00:12:44,610 --> 00:12:47,629
It's like the Bleaucha, nested in
the Scum Pits of Ur.

172
00:12:48,210 --> 00:12:49,750
- I have slain many.
- Really?

173
00:12:50,009 --> 00:12:53,129
Tracking it will be simple.
Killing it, more difficult.

174
00:12:54,210 --> 00:12:55,289
Well, yeah.

175
00:12:55,409 --> 00:12:58,889
All right, then. Groo, you go
with Angel. Let's move out.

176
00:13:05,009 --> 00:13:07,330
I don't think that's
such a great idea.

177
00:13:07,409 --> 00:13:11,309
Me and him. I'm more of a loner,
really. Plus, he's so, like, bulky.

178
00:13:12,210 --> 00:13:13,820
He could slow me down.

179
00:13:14,610 --> 00:13:17,940
He's an experienced warrior.
He should be a great asset.

180
00:13:18,809 --> 00:13:20,139
Here's a nice one.

181
00:13:20,610 --> 00:13:23,000
- That's my favorite broadsword!
- It's fine.

182
00:13:26,009 --> 00:13:28,710
Sure you'll be warm enough?
The sewers are damp.

183
00:13:29,009 --> 00:13:31,570
- I shall be fine.
- Here.

184
00:13:33,210 --> 00:13:34,080
Okay.

185
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:36,799
Let's go.

186
00:13:38,610 --> 00:13:41,210
I'll present this beast's head
to my princess.

187
00:13:42,210 --> 00:13:43,860
Right. She'd love that.

188
00:14:00,409 --> 00:14:03,639
- You sense anything?
- A deep sadness.

189
00:14:07,610 --> 00:14:11,299
My princess. She is unhappy.
I fear I am the cause.

190
00:14:13,009 --> 00:14:16,379
No, she's not unhappy
you're here, Groo.

191
00:14:17,210 --> 00:14:19,529
She's thrilled.

192
00:14:20,210 --> 00:14:22,350
Then what keeps her from me?

193
00:14:23,210 --> 00:14:26,789
There is a distance,
as if her heart is not free.

194
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:31,450
I think maybe she's afraid
to get too close.

195
00:14:32,210 --> 00:14:35,970
She's scared if she does,
she'll lose something.

196
00:14:36,409 --> 00:14:37,419
I would give my soul to--

197
00:14:49,009 --> 00:14:51,750
It is wounded. It bleeds.

198
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:56,090
It's better than bread crumbs.
Let's go.

199
00:15:44,809 --> 00:15:46,000
Come.

200
00:16:19,009 --> 00:16:20,200
You're safe.

201
00:16:22,610 --> 00:16:23,909
Well done.

202
00:16:25,009 --> 00:16:27,149
I must say, excellent.

203
00:16:32,809 --> 00:16:34,950
Well done, I must say.

204
00:16:42,649 --> 00:16:44,370
You think you know someone.

205
00:16:45,049 --> 00:16:48,460
You think your place is secure
and there's a future there.

206
00:16:48,649 --> 00:16:50,440
And then something happens.

207
00:16:51,649 --> 00:16:53,750
No, strike that.
Someone happens.

208
00:16:54,649 --> 00:16:58,929
They insinuate themselves,
pushing you out, taking your place.

209
00:17:02,450 --> 00:17:05,819
What makes you think this other
woman's a witch, Ms. Frakes?

210
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:10,480
Why else would Jerry cheat on me?
We've been engaged eight years.

211
00:17:11,450 --> 00:17:14,220
She had to have put
some kind of a spell on him.

212
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:18,380
I'm looking for it in the original
Greek, if possible. Certainly.

213
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:33,839
You do? Excellent.
Could I get a quote on that?

214
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:36,599
Give me her name. Someone will check.

215
00:17:37,250 --> 00:17:40,269
See if we can find out
if she's a witch.

216
00:17:40,849 --> 00:17:42,390
Hot blond 3-7-1-5-9.

217
00:17:45,049 --> 00:17:48,140
I got these off e-mails I took
from Jerry's computer.

218
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,720
It's gonna--

219
00:17:51,049 --> 00:17:54,349
It's gonna be pretty difficult
to find her based on this.

220
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:58,230
Just follow Jerry.
He'll lead you right to her.

221
00:17:59,450 --> 00:18:00,990
Ms. Frakes here wants us...

222
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:02,900
...to stake out her fiancé.

223
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:05,400
I was trying to explain--

224
00:18:06,049 --> 00:18:09,240
We can spare someone to watch
Ms. Frakes' fiancé. Gunn?

225
00:18:11,450 --> 00:18:14,400
If witchcraft is involved,
we should look into it.

226
00:18:14,450 --> 00:18:15,640
- What's up?
- Gunn.

227
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:18,180
Ms. Frakes needs surveillance.

228
00:18:18,650 --> 00:18:19,950
- If you're free.
- Sure.

229
00:18:20,450 --> 00:18:21,680
She'll fill you in.

230
00:18:22,250 --> 00:18:24,809
- I'll leave it in your hands.
- Sure thing.

231
00:18:26,450 --> 00:18:28,380
We won't let you down.

232
00:18:32,450 --> 00:18:35,150
Maybe they should just do it.
Get it over with.

233
00:18:36,049 --> 00:18:37,210
I'm sorry?

234
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:40,059
Cordy and Groo.
She's being noble for the team.

235
00:18:40,849 --> 00:18:43,589
She should just com-shuk.
That's what she wants.

236
00:18:44,450 --> 00:18:45,569
- May I help you?
- Yes.

237
00:18:45,650 --> 00:18:48,000
Here for Grammaticus'
Third Century Greek Commentaries,

238
00:18:48,650 --> 00:18:52,200
- The GTCGC, I'll be just one moment.
- Thank you.

239
00:18:52,849 --> 00:18:55,519
I mean, why not, you know?
Life's short.

240
